{
  "stem": "13469.5",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We perhaps didn't see it straight away when-- when we got there, but we went into a section of about 12 barracks.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we were allocated to barracks according to male and female.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "This time, Rudy was with us, in the male, with my father and me.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Eve and my mother in another barrack.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We were in Belsen in one of the very few brick-built barracks that they had there-- very large barracks which, presently, is being excavated, actually.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It's about 120 feet long and was divided into several sections.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We were in section D, it was barrack number 11, and we were in section D.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the chief in our barrack was called [?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Pinna, ?] and from Holland, originally German refugee, I think.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But this camp that we were in then, this section of Belsen, was called the [GERMAN] lager, which means the exchange camp.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So they were all people that had the blue stamps from Westerbork, but there were already other people in the camp-- especially there were some Greeks in the camp, very strange why they should be there, from Salonika.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And in particular, a man called [INAUDIBLE], and he was the chief of the star camp, because he got there first.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And there was Dutchman called [?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Joseph Weiss. ?] He became his deputy, because the vast majority of people in the star camp were from Holland-- not necessarily Dutch, because many of them were German refugees like us.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But the vast majority came from Holland, and Dutch was the main language that was spoken in the star camp.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Eventually, more than 4,000 people lived in this star camp, in about 12 barracks.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "So I don't know how many people that is per barrack but quite a lot.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "It was pretty congested.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
